Example
List files in current directory:
<?php
// connect and login to FTP server
$ftp_server = "ftp.example.com";
$ftp_conn = ftp_connect($ftp_server) or die("Could not connect to $ftp_server");
$login = ftp_login($ftp_conn, $ftp_username, $ftp_userpass);
// get file list of current directory
$file_list = ftp_nlist($ftp_conn, ".");
var_dump($file_list);
// close connection
ftp_close($ftp_conn);
?>
Definition and Usage
The ftp_nlist() function returns a list of files in the specified directory on the FTP server.
Syntax
ftp_nlist(
ftp_conn, dir
);
Parameter Values
Parameter
Description
ftp_conn
Required. Specifies the FTP connection to use
dir
Required. Specifies the directory to be listed. Use "." to get the current directory
Technical Details
Return Value:
An array of file names from the specified directory on success, FALSE on failure
PHP Version:
4+

